article.help
  .container-fluid
    section.row-fluid.summary
      .summary.col-sm-3
        h3 EXPLAIN
        p.lead Explain query execution
      .details.col-sm-9
        p
          | Prefix any query with the&nbsp;
          code EXPLAIN
          |  keyword to have Neo4j return the execution plan
          | it would use to execute the query.
          | However, the query is not executed, and Neo4j will make no changes to the database.
        p
          | See&nbsp;
          a(help-topic='query plan') :help QUERY PLAN
          |  for a guide to understanding the query plan output.

        table.table-condensed.table-help
          tr
            th Reference:
            td
              code
                a(href='http://neo4j.com/docs/{{neo4j.version}}/execution-plans.html') Execution Plans
              |  manual page
          tr
            th Related:
            td
              a(help-topic='profile') :help PROFILE
              | &nbsp;
              a(help-topic='query plan') :help QUERY PLAN
              | &nbsp;
    section.row-fluid.example
      .col-sm-9.col-sm-offset-3
        figure
          pre.code.runnable.
            EXPLAIN
            MATCH (n:Person) RETURN n LIMIT 25
          figcaption Show the query plan that would be used to find nodes with the Person label,
            |  without actually executing the plan.
